PX prices edged lower this week in Asia owing to falling upstream crude prices & weak demand amid Covid related restrictions. PX prices slipped around 1% WoW and clocked in at USD 950 M/T.

Copper -2%
Copper prices have dropped in last two weeks as the resurgence of delta virus variant may hinder demand in China. The consumption in the country softened in July, which can be depicted from the declining trend of Copper imports for the fourth straight month.

Brent crude oil -4%
Oil prices declined 4% WoW due to concerns that new restrictions to curb the spread of the Delta variant of the COVID could weaken the global economy and affect the fuel demand.
